Detailed Description

Main calculator for the US National Fire Danger Rating System components and indices.

Parameters
LatThe latitude of the simulation point (decimal degrees eg. 46.125)
FuelModelFuel Model (Fuel model character code eg. "Y", "X", etc....
SlopeClass(1-5)
AvgAnnPrecip(Mean annual total precip (inches))
LT(Use Drought Fuel Load Transfer (boolean)
Cure(Use herbaceous curing (boolean))
isAnnual(Treat herbs as annuals, only allow one greenup per year)
kbdiThresholdStarting KBDI value to beging drought fuel load additions (default is 100)
RegObsHour= 13 Regular observation hour (this is used to prompt the GSI-LFMC calculations to run once a day at this hour)
isReinit= false (Reinitialize flag (boolean): Set to true if Init is being called mid-calculation (Not normally used) ///
Returns
